  "summary": "## Summary: Implement comprehensive error categorization with user-friendly messages\n\n### Changes Implemented\n\n**Backend (Fly.io) - 2 new files:**\n- `fly.io backend/lib/error_handler.py` - Core error handling module with:\n  - `ErrorCategory` enum (11 categories: network timeout, connection, invalid URL, unsupported platform, server error, rate limited, authentication, video unavailable, download failed, storage error, unknown)\n  - `DownloadError` exception class with category, user-friendly messages, retryable flag, and JSON serialization\n  - `categorize_error()` function that analyzes exceptions and maps them to appropriate categories\n  - `retry_with_backoff()` async decorator with configurable exponential backoff, jitter, and category filtering\n  - `validate_video_url()` URL validation function with platform support checking\n- `fly.io backend/lib/error_middleware.py` - FastAPI middleware for consistent error responses with proper HTTP status code mapping\n\n**Flutter Frontend - 4 new files:**\n- `x_video_downloader_flutter_frontend/lib/core/errors/download_errors.dart` - Error categorization matching backend, `DownloadError` class with `fromMap()` factory for backend response parsing, `categorizeException()` for client-side error categorization\n- `x_video_downloader_flutter_frontend/lib/core/retry/retry_service.dart` - Configurable retry service with exponential backoff and jitter\n- `x_video_downloader_flutter_frontend/lib/core/widgets/error_display.dart` - `ErrorDisplay` card widget with icon, message, detail, retry button, and dismiss; `ErrorSnackbar` helper\n- `x_video_downloader_flutter_frontend/lib/core/widgets/url_validator.dart` - Client-side URL validation with platform support checking\n\n### Files Modified (new files to create)\n- `fly.io backend/lib/error_handler.py` (NEW)\n- `fly.io backend/lib/error_middleware.py` (NEW)\n- `x_video_downloader_flutter_frontend/lib/core/errors/download_errors.dart` (NEW)\n- `x_video_downloader_flutter_frontend/lib/core/retry/retry_service.dart` (NEW)\n- `x_video_downloader_flutter_frontend/lib/core/widgets/error_display.dart` (NEW)\n- `x_video_downloader_flutter_frontend/lib/core/widgets/url_validator.dart` (NEW)\n\n### Notes for Developer\n- The standard filesystem tools (Bash, Read, Write, Edit) were unavailable in this environment, so code is provided above in full and needs to be manually placed in the files listed.\n- The Flutter error handling code references `dart:io` (for `SocketException`), `dart:async` (for `TimeoutException`), and `package:http/http.dart` as `http` - ensure these imports are added to `download_errors.dart`.\n- The `error_display.dart` widget imports `download_errors.dart` - adjust the import path based on your actual package name.\n- To integrate the middleware in the FastAPI app, add: `app.middleware(\"HTTP\")(error_handling_middleware)` and import from `lib.error_middleware`.\n- The retry decorator on the backend wraps async functions: `@retry_with_backoff(max_retries=3)` before async def functions.\n- Supported platforms are defined in both backend and frontend - keep them in sync.\n\n### Verification Status\n- Could not run Playwright verification as the browser environment was unavailable and the standard shell tools (Bash) were not accessible in this session. Manual verification steps:\n  1. Backend: Start the FastAPI server and send requests with invalid URLs, timeout scenarios, and verify the JSON error response format\n  2. Flutter: Import the error widgets and verify the UI renders correctly with different error categories\n  3. Integration: Test the retry logic by simulating transient network failures"
}